77 template <typename T>
78 class handle_traits {};
79 
93 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
94 class handle {
95 private:
96  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
97 
98  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> _data;
99  handle(const handle &&) = delete;
100  handle &operator=(const handle &&other) = delete;
101 
102 protected:
103  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == _data.get(); }
104  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
105 
106 public:
110  handle(T t, bool weak = false) : _data(0) { reset(t, weak); }
111 
121  handle() : handle((T)0, true) {}
122 
123  handle(const handle &other) : _data(other._data) {}
124  handle &operator=(const handle &other) {
125  _data = other._data;
126  return *this;
127  }
131  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
132  _data.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
133  }
134 
136  T get(bool allow_emtpy = false) const {
137  T result = _data.get();
138 
139  if (allow_emtpy == false && result == nullptr)
140  throw dnnl::error(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
141  "attempt to use uninitialized object");
142 
143  return result;
144  }
145 
146  bool operator==(const handle &other) const {
147  return other._data.get() == _data.get();
148  }
149  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
150 };

418 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
419  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
420  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
421  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
422  } \
423 \
424  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
425  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
426  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
427  } \
428 \
429  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
430  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
431  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
432  } \
433 \
434  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
435  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
436  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
437  return lhs; \
438  } \
439 \
440  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
441  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
442  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
443  return lhs; \
444  } \
445 \
446  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
447  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
448  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
449  return lhs; \
450  } \
451 \
452  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
453  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
454  }

1355  desc() : data() {}
1356 
1362  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, format_tag aformat_tag) {
1363  validate_dims(adims);
1364  error::wrap_c_api(
1365  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data, (int)adims.size(),
1366  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1367  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1368  convert_to_c(aformat_tag)),
1369  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by tag");
1370  }
1371 
1377  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, const dims &astrides) {
1378  validate_dims(adims);
1379  error::wrap_c_api(
1380  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data, (int)adims.size(),
1381  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1382  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1383  astrides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &astrides[0]),
1384  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by strides");
1385  }
1386 
1390  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &adata) : data(adata) {}
1391 
1393  //
1396  desc submemory_desc(const dims &adims, const dims &offsets) {
1397  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md;
1398  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1399  &sub_md, &data, &adims[0], &offsets[0]),
1400  "could not initialize a sub-memory");
1401  return desc(sub_md);
1402  }
1403 
1405  desc reshape(const dims &adims) {
1406  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md;
1407  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(&out_md, &data,
1408  (int)adims.size(), &adims[0]),
1409  "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1410  return desc(out_md);
1411  }
1412 
1415  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
1416 
1418  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
1419 
1420  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
1421  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
1422  }
1423 
1424  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
1425  };

1830 struct primitive_desc : public handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> {
1831  primitive_desc() = default;
1832 
1836  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
1837  const engine &e, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd) {
1838  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
1839  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
1840  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, e.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
1841  error::wrap_c_api(
1842  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
1843  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
1844  fetch_impl();
1845  }
1846 
1847  engine get_engine() { return engine::query(*this); }
1848 
1849  primitive_attr get_primitive_attr() const {
1850  const_dnnl_primitive_attr_t const_cattr;
1851  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_get_attr(get(), &const_cattr),
1852  "could not get attributes");
1853  dnnl_primitive_attr_t cattr;
1854  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_clone(&cattr, const_cattr),
1855  "could not clone attributes");
1856 
1857  primitive_attr attr;
1858  attr.reset(cattr);
1859  return attr;
1860  }
1861 
1863  const char *impl_info_str() const {
1864  const char *res;
1865  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1866  get(), dnnl_query_impl_info_str, 0, &res),
1867  "could not query implementation info string");
1868  return res;
1869  }
1870 
1872  memory::dim query_s64(query q) const {
1873  memory::dim res;
1874  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1875  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(q), 0, &res);
1876  return status == dnnl_success ? res : 0;
1877  }
1878 
1885  bool next_impl() {
1886  dnnl_status_t status
1887  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
1888  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
1889  error::wrap_c_api(status, "primitive descriptor iterator next failed");
1890 
1891  fetch_impl();
1892  return true;
1893  }
1894 
1896  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
1897  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
1898  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
1899  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md};
1900  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
1901  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
1902  throw error(dnnl_invalid_arguments, "invalid memory query");
1903 
1904  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
1905  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
1906  return memory::desc(*cdesc);
1907  }
1908 
1913  memory::desc scratchpad_desc() const {
1914  return query_md(query::scratchpad_md, 0);
1915  }
1916 
1917 private:
1918  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
1919  void fetch_impl() {
1920  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd
1921  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(pd_iterator.get());
1922  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr ? dnnl_success : dnnl_runtime_error,
1923  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from the iterator");
1924  reset(pd);
1925  }
1926 };
